---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Base title="About Stratum -- Built by a Security Engineer for Multi-Tenancy in Node.js" description="Meet Christian Crank, the security engineer behind Stratum. Born from real MSP/MSSP pain, Stratum brings proper multi-tenancy to the Node.js ecosystem.">

<Nav />

<article class="about">
  <!-- Hero-style author section (no card container) -->
  <div class="about-author">
    <div class="about-headshot-wrap">
      <img src="/headshot.png" alt="Photo of Christian Crank" class="about-headshot" width="120" height="120" />
    </div>
    <div class="about-author-info">
      <h1>Christian Crank</h1>
      <p class="about-title">Owner, Security Engineer</p>
      <p class="about-bio">
        Network security engineer with deep roots in the MSP and MSSP world.
        Years of onboarding clients, building monitoring across fragmented platforms,
        and watching tools fail at the one thing they all need: real multi-tenancy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Origin story -->
  <div class="about-story">
    <h2>The problem that started it all</h2>
    <p>
      If you have worked in managed security, you know the drill. An MSSP manages MSPs.
      MSPs manage clients. Clients sometimes have sub-clients. That is four levels of
      hierarchy, and almost no tooling handles it correctly.
    </p>

    <!-- Hierarchy diagram callout -->
    <div class="about-hierarchy">
      <span class="about-hierarchy-label">The hierarchy Stratum models</span>
      <pre><code>MSSP
  MSP (Partner A)
    Client (Acme Corp)
      SubClient (Acme EU)
  MSP (Partner B)
    Client (Globex Inc)</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>
      Instead of one platform with proper tenant isolation, you end up running
      multiple instances of the same tool. One per MSP, sometimes one per client.
      Monitoring sprawls. Costs balloon. Things get lost between instances. You
      spend more time boxing tooling than actually building solutions for your clients.
    </p>

    <h2>Why Stratum</h2>
    <p>
      Stratum models tenants as a tree, up to 20 levels deep. The hierarchy above
      is not a diagram. It is a real data structure in Stratum. Config flows down
      the tree automatically. Isolation strategies apply per tenant. GDPR compliance
      is built in, not bolted on.
    </p>
    <p>
      Node.js had no serious multi-tenancy library. The ecosystem gap was obvious to
      anyone building B2B SaaS or managed services tooling. Stratum fills that gap.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Closing CTA -->
  <div class="about-cta">
    <div class="about-cta-install">
      <code>npm install @stratum-hq/lib pg</code>
    </div>
    <div class="about-cta-links">
      <a href="https://docs.stratum-hq.org/getting-started/quick-start" class="btn-primary">Read the docs</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum" class="btn-secondary">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

<!-- Person structured data -->
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "Christian Crank",
  "jobTitle": "Security Engineer",
  "image": "https://stratum-hq.org/headshot.png",
  "url": "https://stratum-hq.org/about",
  "worksFor": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Stratum HQ",
    "url": "https://stratum-hq.org"
  }
}
</script>

<Footer />

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-24) var(--space-6) var(--space-8);
  }

  /* Author section - no card, just photo + text */
  .about-author {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .about-headshot-wrap {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 120px;
    height: 120px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    background: var(--surface-2);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .about-headshot {
    width: 120px;
    height: 120px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .about-author-info h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }

  .about-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--sandstone);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-bio {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Story sections */
  .about-story h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-story p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  /* Hierarchy diagram callout */
  .about-hierarchy {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .about-hierarchy-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .about-hierarchy pre {
    background: var(--code-bg);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--accent);
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-hierarchy code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--code-text);
  }

  /* CTA */
  .about-cta {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-cta-install {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--code-text);
  }

  .about-cta-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about {
      padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-4);
    }

    .about-author {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .about-author-info h1 {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .about-title {
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>

</Base>
